comments: Allen (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Osman's (CLE) path and does not deliver the contact.
Osman (CLE) is retreating and makes marginal contact with Dinwiddie (BKN) during his shot attempt.
Thompson (CLE) attempts to retrieve the rebound and makes incidental contact with the back of Dinwiddie's (BKN) head.
Nance Jr. (CLE) and Thompson (CLE) make incidental contact with Prince (BKN) during rebounding.
Allen (BKN) maintains legal guarding position as Clarkson (CLE) initiates the contact during his driving shot attempt.
Clarkson (CLE) wraps Dinwiddie's (BKN) upper half as he attempts to get around the screen.

Thompson (CLE) makes incidental contact with the part of Harris' (BKN) hand that is considered part of the ball and cleanly dislodges him. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was confirmed that Harris (BKN) last touched the ball before it went out of bounds.
Osman (CLE) is already in Dinwiddie's (BKN) path when contact occurs near the free throw line, which Osman does not deliver.
Harris (BKN) legally contests Sexton's (CLE) driving shot attempt.
Thompson (CLE) leverages himself with Allen's (BKN) right shoulder during rebounding.
Allen (BKN) makes contact with Thompson's (CLE) right forearm and affects his put-back attempt.

Prince (BKN) grazes the side of Nance Jr.'s (CLE) head and makes marginal contact with it during rebounding. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.

Prince (BKN) and Sexton (CLE) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was confirmed that Prince (BKN) last touched the ball before it went out of bounds.
Nance Jr. (CLE) and Harris (BKN) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Prince (BKN) and Nance Jr. (CLE) engage and disengage without affecting the other's FOM during the inbound.
Allen (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Sexton's (CLE) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Osman (CLE) makes marginal contact with Dinwiddie's (BKN) during his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Thompson (CLE) establishes himself in a screening position in Temple's (BKN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Temple (BKN) briefly has his hand on Clarkson's (CLE) midsection and slides it off without affecting Clarkson's FOM.
Osman (CLE) makes marginal contact with Harris' (BKN) backside during rebounding. After communicating with the Replay Center, the call on the floor of Harris (BKN) last touching the ball stood.
Dinwiddie (BKN) makes contact across Sexton's (CLE) front as he attempts to defend the hand-off.

Thompson (CLE) makes marginal contact with Allen's (BKN) backside during rebounding. After communicating with the Replay Center, the call on the floor that the ball last touched Harris (BKN) before going out of bounds stood.
Temple (BKN) makes clean contact with the ball after Clarkson (CLE) receives the pass.
Temple (BKN) makes marginal contact with Clarkson (CLE) after his gather.
Dinwiddie (BKN) cleanly blocks Sexton's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Thompson (CLE) and Allen (BKN) briefly engage and disengage off-ball without affecting the other's FOM.
Osman (CLE) legally contests Dinwiddie's (BKN) jump shot attempt and would avoid making contact with Dinwiddie's foot if not for his unnatural leg extension.
Allen (BKN) and Thompson (CLE) engage with one another near half-court, but do not affect the other's FOM as they each remain engaged throughout the possession.
